            <header>
                <h1>Clio Integration Setup</h1>
                <p class="subtitle">Connect QuoteCreator to your Clio account in minutes with secure OAuth authentication.</p>
            </header>

            <div class="highlight-box">
                <p><strong>üîí Secure by Design:</strong> We use industry-standard OAuth 2.0 authentication. We never see or store your Clio password‚Äîauthentication happens directly between you and Clio.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="toc">
                <h3>Quick Navigation</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><a href="#overview">Overview</a></li>
                    <li><a href="#requirements">Requirements</a></li>
                    <li><a href="#setup-steps">Setup Steps</a></li>
                    <li><a href="#using-integration">Using the Integration</a></li>
                    <li><a href="#troubleshooting">Troubleshooting</a></li>
                    <li><a href="#disconnect">Disconnecting</a></li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <h2 id="overview">What You'll Get</h2>
            <p>Once connected, QuoteCreator integrates seamlessly with your Clio account:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Browse your matters:</strong> Search and select from all your Clio matters directly in QuoteCreator</li>
                <li><strong>One-tap uploads:</strong> Send estimate PDFs to the right matter with a single tap</li>
                <li><strong>Automatic organization:</strong> Estimates appear in your matter's Documents section</li>
                <li><strong>Set defaults:</strong> Save frequent client matters for faster estimates</li>
                <li><strong>Connection monitoring:</strong> Automatic re-authentication if your connection expires</li>
            </ul>

            <h2 id="requirements">Before You Start</h2>
            <p>Make sure you have:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>‚úÖ <strong>QuoteCreator installed</strong> on your Android device (<a href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.lexopoly.quotecreator" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Download from Google Play</a>)</li>
                <li>‚úÖ <strong>Active Clio account</strong> with login credentials</li>
                <li>‚úÖ <strong>Internet connection</strong> for initial setup</li>
                <li>‚úÖ <strong>Permission to connect apps</strong> (if you're on a firm-managed Clio account, check with your admin)</li>
            </ul>

            <div class="warning-box">
                <p><strong>‚ö†Ô∏è Firm-Managed Accounts:</strong> If you're part of a law firm with admin-managed Clio access, check with your IT administrator before connecting third-party apps. Some firms restrict integrations for security compliance.</p>
            </div>

            <h2 id="setup-steps">Setup Steps</h2>

            <div class="step-box">
                <h3><span class="step-number">1</span> Open QuoteCreator Settings</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Open the <strong>QuoteCreator</strong> app on your Android device</li>
                    <li>Tap the <strong>‚öôÔ∏è Settings</strong> icon (usually in the top-right corner or bottom navigation)</li>
                    <li>Scroll to the <strong>Integrations</strong> section</li>
                    <li>Find <strong>Clio Integration</strong> and tap <strong>Connect to Clio</strong></li>
                </ol>
            </div>

            <div class="step-box">
                <h3><span class="step-number">2</span> Complete Manual OAuth Authorization</h3>
                <p><strong>‚ö†Ô∏è Important:</strong> This is a manual copy/paste process. QuoteCreator will open your browser, then you'll need to copy the authorization code back to the app.</p>

                <h4 style="margin-top: 1.5rem; color: var(--accent);">Step 2A: Authorize in Your Browser</h4>
                <ol>
                    <li>QuoteCreator automatically <strong>opens your browser</strong> to the Clio authorization page</li>
                    <li>Enter your <strong>Clio email and password</strong> (we never see this)</li>
                    <li>Review the permissions QuoteCreator is requesting:
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Read matters:</strong> To browse and search your client matters</li>
                            <li><strong>Write documents:</strong> To upload estimate PDFs to matters</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li>Click <strong>"Allow Access"</strong> to authorize</li>
                </ol>

                <h4 style="margin-top: 1.5rem; color: var(--accent);">Step 2B: Copy Code from "Can't Reach This Site" Page</h4>
                <ol start="5">
                    <li>After clicking "Allow", your browser will show <strong>"Can't reach this site"</strong> or similar error</li>
                    <li><strong>This is normal!</strong> Look at the <strong>URL in your browser's address bar</strong></li>
                    <li>The URL will look like: <code style="background: #f0f0f0; padding: 2px 6px; border-radius: 4px; font-family: monospace;">http://127.0.0.1:5001/callback?code=AbCdEf123...</code></li>
                    <li><strong>Copy the entire URL</strong> from the address bar (or just the code after <code>code=</code>)</li>
                </ol>

                <div class="highlight-box" style="margin-top: 1.5rem; background: #fffbeb; border-left-color: var(--warning);">
                    <p><strong>üì± What You'll See in Your Browser:</strong></p>
                    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">After clicking "Allow Access", the browser shows:</p>
                    <ul style="margin-bottom: 0; margin-left: 1.5rem;">
                        <li><strong>"This site can't be reached"</strong> or <strong>"Unable to connect"</strong></li>
                        <li>URL in address bar: <code style="background: white; padding: 2px 6px; border-radius: 4px; font-family: monospace; font-size: 0.85rem;">http://127.0.0.1:5001/callback?code=...</code></li>
                        <li><strong>Don't close this page yet!</strong> You need to copy the URL first</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <h4 style="margin-top: 1.5rem; color: var(--accent);">Step 2C: Paste Code Into QuoteCreator</h4>
                <ol start="9">
                    <li><strong>Switch back to QuoteCreator</strong> (use app switcher or tap QuoteCreator icon)</li>
                    <li>You'll see <strong>"Paste Authorization Code"</strong> screen with a text field</li>
                    <li><strong>Paste the URL or code</strong> into the field (QuoteCreator will extract the code automatically)</li>
                    <li>Tap <strong>"Continue"</strong> to complete authorization</li>
                </ol>

                <div class="warning-box" style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">
                    <p><strong>üí° Pro Tips:</strong></p>
                    <ul style="margin-bottom: 0;">
                        <li><strong>Split-screen mode:</strong> If your device supports it, keep QuoteCreator and browser visible at once</li>
                        <li><strong>Copy the entire URL:</strong> Don't worry about extracting just the code‚Äîpaste the whole URL and QuoteCreator will parse it</li>
                        <li><strong>Address bar, not error message:</strong> Copy from the address bar at the top, not the error text on the page</li>
                        <li><strong>Codes expire quickly:</strong> If it doesn't work, start over from Step 1 within a few minutes</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <p style="margin-top: 1.5rem;"><strong>üîê Security Note:</strong> Your Clio password stays with Clio‚Äîwe only receive a secure access token that allows QuoteCreator to perform the actions you approve.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="step-box">
                <h3><span class="step-number">3</span> Confirm Connection</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>You'll be redirected back to <strong>QuoteCreator</strong></li>
                    <li>You'll see a <strong>‚úÖ Connected to Clio</strong> success message</li>
                    <li>Your Clio account email will be displayed in Settings</li>
                    <li>Connection status will show as <strong>Active</strong></li>
                </ol>
            </div>

            <div class="success-box">
                <p><strong>‚úÖ Setup Complete!</strong> You can now upload estimates directly to your Clio matters. See the next section for usage instructions.</p>
            </div>

            <h2 id="using-integration">Using the Clio Integration</h2>

            <h3>Creating an Estimate with Clio Upload</h3>
            <ol>
                <li><strong>Create your estimate</strong> as usual (add line items, pricing, etc.)</li>
                <li>Tap <strong>"Select Matter"</strong> in the estimate details</li>
                <li><strong>Browse or search</strong> your Clio matters by:
                    <ul>
                        <li>Client name</li>
                        <li>Matter description</li>
                        <li>Matter number</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li><strong>Select the correct matter</strong> and tap <strong>Confirm</strong></li>
                <li>Complete your estimate and tap <strong>Generate PDF</strong></li>
                <li>Tap <strong>Share</strong> ‚Üí <strong>Send to Clio</strong></li>
                <li>Confirm the upload‚Äîyour PDF will appear in the matter's Documents section</li>
            </ol>

            <h3>Setting Default Matters</h3>
            <p>For frequent clients, you can set a default matter to save time:</p>
            <ol>
                <li>Open an estimate for your frequent client</li>
                <li>Select their matter as usual</li>
                <li>Tap the <strong>‚≠ê Set as Default</strong> option</li>
                <li>Next time you create an estimate for this customer, the matter will auto-populate</li>
            </ol>

            <h3>Verifying Uploads</h3>
            <p>To confirm your estimate was uploaded successfully:</p>
            <ol>
                <li>Log in to <a href="https://app.clio.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Clio</a></li>
                <li>Navigate to the client matter</li>
                <li>Open the <strong>Documents</strong> tab</li>
                <li>Look for your estimate PDF (named with the estimate number and date)</li>
            </ol>

            <h2 id="troubleshooting">Troubleshooting</h2>

            <div class="troubleshooting-item">
                <h4>‚ùå "Connection Failed" Error</h4>
                <p><strong>Problem:</strong> Unable to connect to Clio during setup.</p>
                <p class="solution">‚úÖ Solution:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Check your internet connection (WiFi or mobile data)</li>
                    <li>Verify your Clio login credentials are correct</li>
                    <li>Try logging in to <a href="https://app.clio.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Clio</a> in your browser first</li>
                    <li>Restart QuoteCreator and try again</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="troubleshooting-item">
                <h4>‚ùå "No Matters Found"</h4>
                <p><strong>Problem:</strong> Matter browser shows empty list.</p>
                <p class="solution">‚úÖ Solution:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Verify you have active matters in your Clio account</li>
                    <li>Check that matters aren't archived (QuoteCreator only shows active matters)</li>
                    <li>Try refreshing the matter list (pull down to refresh)</li>
                    <li>Disconnect and reconnect your Clio integration</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="troubleshooting-item">
                <h4>‚ùå "Upload Failed" Error</h4>
                <p><strong>Problem:</strong> PDF won't upload to Clio matter.</p>
                <p class="solution">‚úÖ Solution:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Check your internet connection</li>
                    <li>Verify the matter still exists and is active in Clio</li>
                    <li>Ensure you have permission to upload documents to the matter</li>
                    <li>Try re-authenticating your Clio connection</li>
                    <li>Generate the PDF again and retry the upload</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="troubleshooting-item">
                <h4>‚ùå "Session Expired" Warning</h4>
                <p><strong>Problem:</strong> Clio access token expired after 30+ days of inactivity.</p>
                <p class="solution">‚úÖ Solution:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Tap <strong>Re-authenticate</strong> when prompted</li>
                    <li>You'll be redirected to Clio to re-authorize access</li>
                    <li>No data is lost‚Äîyour estimates remain intact</li>
                    <li>Connection will be restored automatically</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="warning-box">
                <p><strong>Still Having Issues?</strong> Contact our support team at <a href="mailto:support@lexopoly.com">support@lexopoly.com</a> with:
                <ul>
                    <li>The error message you're seeing</li>
                    <li>Your Android device model and OS version</li>
                    <li>Whether you're using WiFi or mobile data</li>
                    <li>Any recent changes to your Clio account</li>
                </ul>
                We typically respond within 24 hours (weekdays).</p>
            </div>

            <h2 id="disconnect">Disconnecting from Clio</h2>

            <h3>From QuoteCreator</h3>
            <p>To disconnect your Clio integration from QuoteCreator:</p>
            <ol>
                <li>Open <strong>QuoteCreator Settings</strong></li>
                <li>Go to <strong>Integrations ‚Üí Clio Integration</strong></li>
                <li>Tap <strong>Disconnect from Clio</strong></li>
                <li>Confirm the disconnection</li>
            </ol>
            <p>This will delete all Clio access tokens from your device. Your estimates remain intact, but you won't be able to upload to Clio until you reconnect.</p>

            <h3>From Clio (Revoke Access)</h3>
            <p>To permanently revoke QuoteCreator's access from the Clio side:</p>
            <ol>
                <li>Log in to <a href="https://app.clio.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Clio</a></li>
                <li>Go to <strong>Settings ‚Üí Integrations ‚Üí Connected Apps</strong></li>
                <li>Find <strong>QuoteCreator</strong> in the list</li>
                <li>Click <strong>Revoke Access</strong></li>
                <li>Confirm the revocation</li>
            </ol>
            <p>This prevents QuoteCreator from accessing your Clio account, even if you reinstall the app. You'll need to re-authorize if you want to reconnect later.</p>

            <h2>Privacy & Security</h2>
            <p>Your data security is our top priority:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>No password storage:</strong> We never see or store your Clio password</li>
                <li><strong>OAuth 2.0:</strong> Industry-standard secure authentication</li>
                <li><strong>Encrypted tokens:</strong> Access tokens stored with Android KeyStore encryption</li>
                <li><strong>HTTPS only:</strong> All Clio API requests use TLS 1.2+ encryption</li>
                <li><strong>Local-first:</strong> Estimates stay on your device until you explicitly upload</li>
                <li><strong>No data sale:</strong> We never sell or share your business data</li>
            </ul>
            <p>For complete details, see our <a href="/quotecreator/privacy/">Privacy Policy</a>.</p>

